      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "Muslim Aid America's financial health is bolstered by a <cite id=\"11\">3-year revenue CAGR of 24.2%</cite>, demonstrating rapid growth and increasing donor trust. This growth supports a wide array of programs, including <cite id=\"12\">healthcare and education initiatives</cite> in underserved regions. The organization's governance is overseen by an <cite id=\"13\">independent board of 9 members</cite>, ensuring that 100% of board members are independent and providing strong oversight of its <cite id=\"14\">$26.1 million in annual revenue</cite>."
      ],
      "summary": "Muslim Aid America is a humanitarian organization dedicated to assisting individuals suffering from <cite id=\"1\">hunger, disease, and illiteracy across the globe</cite>. The organization operates with a mission to provide <cite id=\"2\">emergency relief, water and sanitation, and food security</cite> to victims of natural disasters and conflict. In the 2023 fiscal year, the organization reported <cite id=\"3\">total revenue of $26,177,076</cite>, reflecting a significant capacity to address urgent global needs. Their financial model is characterized by a <cite id=\"4\">program expense ratio of 93.2%</cite>, indicating that nearly all funds are directed toward direct service delivery. Furthermore, the charity demonstrates <cite id=\"5\">exceptional fundraising efficiency</cite>, spending only <cite id=\"6\">$0.04 to raise every $1</cite>. While the organization serves diverse regions including <cite id=\"7\">Africa, Asia, and the Middle East</cite>, it maintains a lean operational structure with <cite id=\"8\">2.1 months of working capital</cite> to manage its global programs.",
